<h1>Problem 1175 - 2022 Israel TST 8, P3, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>In triangle \(ABC\), the angle bisectors are \(BE\) and \(CF\) (where \(E, F\) are on the sides of the triangle), and their intersection point is \(I\). Point \(N\) lies on the circumcircle of \(AEF\), and the angle \(\angle IAN\) is right. The circumcircle of \(AEF\) meets the line \(NI\) a second time at the point \(L\). Show that the circumcenter of \(AIL\) lies on line \(BC\).</p>
